.TH HSH 1 "1 Nov 2021" "0.1" "HSH"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- command line interpreter (simple shell)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
The hsh shell is a simple shell which serves as a user interface through which users interact with Uni-like operating systems. It is a cpmmand line interpreter that executes commands and also scripting languahe.

.B Overview

The shell prompts users to type commands directly into the interface or through a file, reads lines from the file or terminal, then executes the command

.B Interactive mode

A user can interact with the shell by typing inputs using the keybooard

.B Non-interactive mode

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns the error code given by the last completed command followed by either ctrl-d or exit with no status code.

.SH
The shell has some builtins that replicate other unix shell builtins

.SH SYNTAX
$ <command> <flags or options> <argument 1> <argument 2> ...
OR NON-INTERACTIVE MODE:
$ <command> | ./hsh
.SS
Interactive mode:

.SS
EXAMPLE 1:
$ /bin/ls
.SS
EXAMPLE 2:
$ ls -l

.SH EXIT

The shell exits with a non zero exit status when errors are detected. Depending on the shell, the execution may be aborted

.SH BUGS
No known bugs

